race.description: Btc Constructions Melbourne Cup Day On Sale Handicap
race.comment: The former Victorian TIPSY TORONADO (5) was beaten 1.5L resuming for the new yard then progressed nicely last time out to score as public elect over 1200m in a 58. Carries just 1.5kg more and will jump fitter from an inside gate. She can go right on with the job. PATRIOTIC KING (2) just missed twice before delivering a 58 over 1000m. Did it comfortably heavily backed and it is hard to risk the leading jockey/stable combo. MERCHANT DELIGHT (1) led a month ago and made it 2/3 this preparation taking out a 58 over 1300m. The shorter sprint is a niggle but he will use the rails gate and has a handy 3kg claim. SOUL SPIRIT (7) led and showed enough placing last time to fill a slot.
